# ArtLomo Chat Kickoff Contract

**Last Updated:** Mar 9, 2026

This is the streamlined startup contract for conversations in the
ArtLomo repository.
If any rule here conflicts with `/srv/artlomo/.windsurfrules`,
the Windsurf rules win.

## 1) Mandatory Startup Context

Before significant edits (especially multi-file or structural changes), read:

1. `/srv/artlomo/README.md`
2. `/srv/artlomo/application/docs/ARCHITECTURE_INDEX.md`
3. `/srv/artlomo/application/docs/SYSTEM_MAP.md`
4. `/srv/artlomo/application/docs/DEFINITION_OF_DONE.md`
5. `/srv/artlomo/application/docs/rules-&-parameters.md`
6. `/srv/artlomo/CHANGELOG.md`

For tooling/ops documentation tasks, also read:

1. `/srv/artlomo/application/docs/TOOLS_SH_COVERAGE_REPORT_2026-03-07.md`

If changing more than 2 files, explicitly state this exact line
before proposing edits:

"I am referencing MASTER_FILE_INDEX.md and SYSTEM_MAP.md to ensure
structural alignment."

If ownership, boundaries, or architecture change, update
`ARCHITECTURE_INDEX.md` in the same task.

## 2) Golden Loop

- Pre-flight: Identify workflow scope (`upload`, `analysis`, `artwork`,
  `mockups`, `manual`, `export`, `admin`, `video`), confirm
  ownership/dependencies, and search before editing.
- Execution: Keep fixes minimal and root-cause oriented. Business logic
  belongs in services. Routes orchestrate HTTP only. UI contains no
  business logic.
- Post-flight: Run targeted verification for touched code and validate
  against Definition of Done.

## 3) Layered Architecture (Non-Negotiable)

- Layer 1: Core (`application/utils`, `application/common/utilities`, config)
- Layer 2: Services (business logic)
- Layer 3: Routes (HTTP orchestration)
- Layer 4: UI (templates/static)

Rules:

- Dependency direction only `4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 1`
- No cross-workflow imports at Layer 2
- Shared logic goes in `application/common` or `application/utils`
- `application/utils` must not import workflow/domain logic

## 4) Workflow Isolation

Each workflow owns its routes, services, UI, and domain models in its folder.
No unscoped global UI handlers.
Delete UX is workflow-owned (no global delete handlers).

## 5) Critical Invariants

### Artwork Single-State Invariant

A slug exists in exactly one location:

- `lab/unprocessed/{slug}/`
- `lab/processed/{slug}/`
- `lab/locked/{slug}/`

Promotions must be atomic moves (`shutil.move`), never copy and delete.
Reanalysis edits in place; never duplicate slug folders.

### Database Sync Invariant

Any analysis promotion (OpenAI/Gemini/Manual) must set DB status to `processed`.

## 6) Image, Mockup, and Detail-Closeup Standards

Use config constants only (no hardcoded dimensions).

- ANALYSE: 2048 long edge
- THUMB: 500x500 center crop
- MOCKUP COMPOSITE: 2048 long edge
- DETAIL CLOSEUP: 2048 output
- DETAIL PROXY: 7200 long edge at 90% quality

Detail closeup v2.1:

- Frontend normalization uses `offsetWidth` and `offsetHeight`
- Save endpoint uses `norm_x` and `norm_y` in `[0.0, 1.0]`, default `0.5`
- Zoom must preserve center pixel (no jump)
- No debug noise in production

Mockup coordinates v2.0:

- `format_version: "2.0"`
- `zones[].points`: exactly 4 points in order `TL, TR, BR, BL`
- No crossed quads (bow-ties)
- 4px outward bleed required
- Composite order: artwork first, base PNG last

Mockup base source of truth:

- `application/mockups/catalog/assets/mockups/bases/{aspect}/{category}/`
- Admin category counts derive from filesystem `*.png`
- Sanitize and Sync normalizes filenames and generates 500x500 thumbs

## 7) UI and Styling Contract (Strict)

- No inline styles
- No inline JavaScript (`<script>...</script>` blocks in templates)
- No inline event handlers (`onclick`, `onchange`, `onsubmit`, etc.)
- No hardcoded hex colors in HTML or JS
- No utility classes that break theme toggles

Use global CSS variables only:

- Background: `var(--bg-main)` and `var(--bg-card)`
- Text: `var(--text-main)` and `var(--text-muted)`
- Borders: `1px solid var(--border-color)`
- Keep UI flat and structural, no heavy blurred shadows
- Primary actions: `var(--accent-orange)`
- Destructive actions only: `var(--danger-red)`

Layout rules:

- Keep hierarchy compact and high-density
- Header bars use flex with breadcrumb/title on one row

## 8) Jinja2 Preservation

- Preserve all Jinja2 logic (`{% ... %}`, `{{ ... }}`)
- Do not alter backend loops to force frontend layout
- Do not replace existing template variables with placeholders

## 9) Async and Polling Behavior

Upload polling:

- Status file: `lab/unprocessed/{slug}/processing_status.json`
- UI endpoint: `/artworks/{slug}/status` every 1000ms
- No percent progress bars (stage labels only)

Analysis loading:

- Use `analysis-loading.js` and `analysis-loading.css`
- Poll `/api/analysis/status/{slug}` until done
- Redirect to `/artwork/{slug}/review/{provider}`

## 10) Security Requirements

- All mutating endpoints enforce CSRF (`require_csrf_or_400`)
- `fetch` requests must send `X-CSRFToken`
- Validate slug/path with safe helpers (`slug_sku`)
- Log security-sensitive actions via `logger_utils.log_security_event`

## 11) Logging and Completion

- Log success and failure to `/srv/artlomo/logs/` where appropriate
- Clean up temporary files after image and video processing
- A task is complete only when `DEFINITION_OF_DONE.md` is satisfied

## 12) Editing Conduct

- Prefer targeted diffs over broad rewrites
- Keep imports at top
- Add comments only for non-obvious logic
- Never revert unrelated local changes

## 13) Markdown Authoring and Lint Contract (Mandatory for All `.md` Files)

Markdown changes are not complete until lint is clean for touched files.

Authoring rules (must follow while writing):

- Use ATX headings only (`#`, `##`, `###`) with one space after `#`.
- Keep one blank line before and after headings, lists, tables,
  and fenced code blocks.
- Use fenced code blocks with an explicit language
  (` ```bash`, ` ```python`, ` ```json`, etc.).
- Use `-` for unordered lists; keep list indentation consistent
  (`0` or `2` spaces only where structurally required).
- Ordered lists must be sequential (`1.`, `2.`, `3.`),
  never repeated `1.` style.
- Wrap prose to 80 characters where practical to satisfy line-length checks
  (reflow sentences instead of leaving long lines).
- Avoid duplicate headings at the same level in a file;
  make headings unique and descriptive.
- No trailing spaces and no tabs.
- In table cells, do not use raw `|` as text content.
  Use commas, `\\|`, or inline code that does not break cell count.
- Do not emit placeholder text like `TBD`, `TODO`,
  `lorem ipsum`, or `...` in final docs.

Mandatory markdownlint rules to satisfy:

- MD007, MD009, MD013, MD022, MD024, MD026, MD029, MD031, MD032,
  MD040, MD056, MD060

Required verification workflow for any touched `.md` files:

1. Run auto-fix first:
  `npx markdownlint-cli2 --fix <touched-markdown-files>`
2. Run validation second:
  `npx markdownlint-cli2 <touched-markdown-files>`
3. If any errors remain, manually correct them and re-run validation
  until zero errors.

Safety constraints:

- Do not run recursive markdown fixers across the whole repository
  unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer targeted file lists over broad scans.
- If a file cannot be made clean without major semantic rewriting,
  stop and call out the exact blocking lines.

